<%# landing-page: standalone marketing / SEO page (app/views/public), not part of a user's blog %>
<%= content_for :title do %>
  about.me alternative with a blog and custom domain — Pagecord
<% end %>

<%= content_for :og_image do %>
  <%= dynamic_og_image_for_landing_page(title: "A Better about.me Alternative") %>
<% end %>

<%= content_for :meta_description do %>
  An about.me alternative with a homepage, blog, pages, RSS, email subscribers, custom domains, and export. Free forever or $39/year.
<% end %>

<div class="md:mt-4 mb-4 md:mb-8 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4">
  <h1 class="source-serif font-semibold text-center text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">
    about.me is a profile page. Pagecord is a whole personal site.
  </h1>

  <div class="md:text-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 flex flex-col gap-y-4">
    <p class="mt-8 md:mt-12">
      A profile page is useful when all you need is a name, a photo, and a handful of links. But people are more than links.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pagecord gives you the profile page, then lets it grow: a homepage, a blog, pages for About, Now, Contact, or Portfolio, RSS, email subscribers, themes, custom domains, and publishing from your inbox.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you are starting from scratch, see how Pagecord works as a <%= link_to "personal website with a blog", personal_website_path, class: "home-link" %>.
    </p>
    <p>
      No AI gimmick required. Classic is free forever. Premium is $<%= localised_price %>/year.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="text-center mt-8 mb-4 md:text-xl">
    <%= link_to new_signup_path do %>
      <div class="mt-2 inline-flex font-medium p-4 rounded-xl shadow-sm btn-primary text-xl">Create your free Pagecord account</div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "screenshots" %>

